    <div id="talks" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#accordionWorks">
      <div class="accordion-body">
        <strong>Some of the slides i used for beamer talks are collected below, and maybe some recordings.</strong> <br>
        They are grouped by topics, variations on a same theme, and then appear in (anti)chronological order. 
        One must often adapt presentations for different audiences and durations.
      
      <ul>
           <li> <i> Linking numbers of modular knots. </i>
           The <a href="talkslides/2022-06-24_SouThese_AriTopoNoeMod.pdf">slides in French</a> for my PhD defense.
           Similar <a href="talkslides/2022-12-22_AriTopoNoeMod_UJF.pdf"> slides in French</a> for a talk at UJF .
           Similar <a href="talkslides/2022-11-16_ATMK_Brown.pdf"> slides in English</a> for a talk at Brown University. 
           </li>
           
           <li> <i> Character varieties of surface groups. </i>
           The <a href="talkslides/.pdf">slides in French</a> for my PhD defense.
           The <a href="talkslides/.pdf"> slides </a>. 
           The <a href="talkslides/.pdf"> slides </a>. 
           </li>
           
           <li> <i> Topology et dénombrement des courbes algébriques réelles </i>
           Some <a href="talkslides/.pdf">slides in French</a> (combinatorics of analytic chord diagrams).
           Some <a href="talkslides/.pdf"> slides in French</a> (geometry of real analytic singular curves). 
           Some <a href="talkslides/.pdf"> slides in English</a> (combinatorics of real algebraic curves and their interlace graphs). 
           </li>

