      <div class="accordion-body">
        <strong>Various outreach documents.</strong>
        They appear in (anti)chronological order.
      
      <ul>
           <li> <i> Images des maths  </i>
               An <a href= >article</a> on the online expository journal <a> Image des mathématiques</a> about elastic energy and bouncing balls.
            </li>
            
            <li> <b> Interview </b> by Etienne Ghys for his podcast series <i>Petites histoires de sciences</i>.
            Podcast <a href=https://www.canalacademies.com/emissions/petites-histoires-de-science/mathematiciens-daujourdhui/christopher-lloyd-simon-un-jeune-docteur-de-26-ans-amoureux-des-maths> link </a>.
            </li>
            
            <li> <i> Topolo-geometrical entries to the blog of the 2017 geometry workshop at Stony Brook</a> </i>.
            While taking part in the 2017 <a href=https://workshop2017web.wordpress.com/>geometry workshop</a>
            held by Moira Chas, Tony Phillips and Dennis Sullivan, I wrote a couple of blog entries 
            about <a href=https://workshop2017web.wordpress.com/2017/07/08/mobius-euler-and-arithmetical-functions/>Möbius, Euler and Dirichlet series</a>,
            <a href=https://workshop2017web.wordpress.com/2017/06/01/iterative-thurston-simple-curve/>iterating Thurston's simple curve</a>,
            <a href=https://workshop2017web.wordpress.com/2017/05/27/the-space-of-all-hyperbolic-metrics/> moduli space of hyperbolic metrics</a>, 
            <a href=https://workshop2017web.wordpress.com/2017/05/26/what-do-dentist-change/> Dehn twists</a>.
            </li>
         </ul>
